Add assertions for null and argument validation
commitResults.messageBody: Introduced assert statements throughout the codebase to ensure method arguments and important fields are not null or invalid. This improves code robustness by catching programming errors early, especially in constructors, command execution, and utility methods.

commitResults.messageTitle: Remove redundant Javadoc and refactor constants
commitResults.messageBody: Eliminated excessive Javadoc comments and simplified code across commands, tasks, and utility classes. Promoted magic strings and numbers to constants for maintainability. Improved code readability and consistency, especially in command parsing and task serialization.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add sort command for task list with multiple criteria
commitResults.messageBody: Introduces a SortCommand to allow sorting tasks by description, deadline, event start, type, or status. TaskList now provides sorting methods for each criterion. Parser is updated to recognize and parse the new 'sort' command. Ui and GuiUi are updated to support a showMessage method for consistent message display.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add assertions for null and argument validation (#11)
commitResults.messageBody: Introduced assert statements throughout the codebase to ensure method arguments and important fields are not null or invalid. This improves code robustness by catching programming errors early, especially in constructors, command execution, and utility methods.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor Duke references to Lyra in dialog code
commitResults.messageBody: Renamed getDukeDialog to getLyraDialog in DialogBox and updated all usages in Launcher. Also removed unused imports from several files for code cleanliness.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update main class path in test scripts
commitResults.messageBody: Changed the Java main class reference in both runtest.bat and runtest.sh from 'Lyra' and 'duke.Lyra' to 'lyra.Lyra' to ensure correct execution of the test scripts.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor Duke references to Lyra in dialog code (#12)
commitResults.messageBody:
* Refactor Duke references to Lyra in dialog code

Renamed getDukeDialog to getLyraDialog in DialogBox and updated all usages in Launcher. Also removed unused imports from several files for code cleanliness.

* Update main class path in test scripts

Changed the Java main class reference in both runtest.bat and runtest.sh from 'Lyra' and 'duke.Lyra' to 'lyra.Lyra' to ensure correct execution of the test scripts.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add help command and improve UI/UX feedback
commitResults.messageBody: Introduces a new HelpCommand to display all available commands and usage tips. Enhances the FindCommand with better feedback when no matches are found. Updates the Parser to recognize the 'help' command and improves error messages. Refines the DialogBox and Launcher UI for a more modern look and better usability. Updates welcome message in Ui. Improves TaskListTest to handle assertion errors and LyraException in edge cases.

commitResults.messageTitle: Redesign UI with modern styles and improved dialogs
commitResults.messageBody: Refactors DialogBox to use asymmetric layouts and modern message styling for user, bot, error, and success dialogs. Updates Launcher to apply a modern gradient background, enhance input and button styles, and display success and error messages with distinct dialog types. Improves layout responsiveness and overall user experience.

commitResults.messageTitle: Revamp user guide and add UI screenshot
commitResults.messageBody: Updated docs/README.md with comprehensive instructions, feature list, command reference, usage examples, troubleshooting, and support information for Lyra. Added docs/Ui.png as a GUI screenshot to enhance documentation.
